"Lambda is an anonymous function. In Od, both body and arguments of lambda are
put inside { curly brackets }, and are separated by arrow. If list of arguments
is empty, arrow can be omit, too."

    map [1, 2, 3] to { x -> x + 2 }

    if todayIsABigDay then {
        print "Today is a big day!"
    } else {
        print "Don't worry, today is okay, too."
    }

"As you can see, if-then-else is a method call on a boolean. But it looks pretty
much the same as a normal if-then-else!"
